places.name: Bellevue Downtown Park
places.description: Lushly planted city park featuring a 240-foot-wide waterfall, a picnic green & a playground. Perfect for family outings with wide open spaces, peaceful walking paths, and the famous Inspiration Playground designed for all abilities.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking available in multiple lots including Southern Parking Lot
places.specialNotes: Features the famous 240-foot waterfall, duck pond, and the Inspiration Playground. Dog-friendly with designated areas. Great for jogging, walking, or family picnics. Open 24 hours.

yunsolExperience.likes: The waterfall is mesmerizing for Yunsol! She could watch the ducks for hours and loves the Inspiration Playground.
yunsolExperience.dislikes: The walking paths can be long for little legs. Some areas get muddy after rain.
yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The duck pond is magical in the morning. Bring breadcrumbs (if allowed) and a stroller for the longer walks. The playground is perfect for her age group - safe but challenging!

places.name: Great Wolf Lodge Water Park
places.description: Indoor/outdoor water park resort with slides, pools, and activities designed for families. Features themed water attractions, arcade games, and on-site dining options perfect for a full day or weekend adventure.
places.parkingInfo: Paid parking available on-site for resort guests and day pass visitors
places.specialNotes: 3-star resort with water park access. Check-in 4:00 PM, Check-out 11:00 AM. LGBTQ+ friendly. Off I-5, 7 miles from Centralia Rollerdrome. Day passes available for water park access. Multiple restaurants on-site including Lodge Wood Fired Grill and buffet options.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for toddlers who love water! Indoor water park means weather won't affect plans. Consider staying overnight for the full experience.

places.name: Tukwila Family Fun Center & Bullwinkle's Restaurant
places.description: Amusement park with go-karts, bumper boats, mini-golf & many other activities, plus pizza & burgers. Perfect for active toddlers and families looking for diverse entertainment options.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking available on-site with large parking lot
places.specialNotes: Wristbands available for multiple activities. Value packages starting at $60. Open 11 AM Thu. Features go-karts, laser tag, bowling, mini golf, and arcade. On-site restaurant with kid-friendly menu. Great for birthday parties and group events.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Lots of activities under one roof - perfect for energetic toddlers! Check height requirements for go-karts. The arcade will definitely be a hit!

places.name: Gene Coulon Memorial Beach Park
places.description: Public 57-acre lakeside park offering boat launches, a walking trail, tennis courts & picnic areas. Features a beautiful mile-long walkway along Lake Washington with amazing sunset views.
places.address: 1201 Lake Washington Blvd N, Renton, WA 98056
places.parkingInfo: Free parking available but can be limited during peak times. Multiple parking areas including boat launch parking
places.specialNotes: Open 8 AM daily. Features mile-long lakeside walkway, swimming area with beach, volleyball courts, tennis courts, BBQ grills, boat launch and docks. On-site restaurants include Ivar's Seafood Bar and Kidd Valley. Spectacular sunset views. Well-maintained with restrooms and picnic facilities.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The walking path along the lake is perfect for strollers! Swimming area and playground will keep Yunsol busy. Great spot for family picnics with restaurant options nearby.

places.name: Westfield Southcenter
places.description: 2-level indoor shopping mall with more than 200 stores & eateries plus a multiplex with IMAX. Perfect for rainy days with kid-friendly activities and diverse dining options.
places.parkingInfo: Free huge parking lots with multiple levels and easy access
places.specialNotes: Open 10 AM daily. Features movie theater with IMAX, extensive food court with Asian cuisine, and kids' car rides on the second floor. Over 200 stores including major department stores. Climate-controlled environment perfect for any weather. Wide hallways and wheelchair accessible.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great backup plan for rainy days! The kids' car rides will be a hit with Yunsol. Food court has lots of options, and it's perfect for shopping while keeping little ones entertained.

places.name: Newcastle Beach Park
places.description: This grassy park has a beach with docks & lifeguards, restrooms, picnic tables & a play area. Beautiful location with clean sand, clear water, and stunning sunset views.
places.address: 4400 Lake Washington Blvd SE, Bellevue, WA 98006
places.parkingInfo: Limited parking spaces available, can fill up quickly during peak times
places.specialNotes: Open 6 AM daily. Features lifeguarded swimming area, fishing pier, picnic sites, and playground. Note: Swimming may be restricted due to water quality (bacteria levels). Dog-friendly with leash requirements. Beautiful sunset views and calm atmosphere perfect for family relaxation.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Beautiful beach setting with playground! Check water quality before planning to swim. The calm atmosphere and sunset views make it perfect for peaceful family time.

places.name: Lake Boren Park
places.description: Local park with walking paths, a kids' play area, picnic shelters, a fishing dock & athletic courts. Well-maintained grounds with lots of open space and activities for all ages.
places.parkingInfo: Free on-site parking available with good accessibility
places.specialNotes: Open 8 AM daily. Features tennis courts, basketball courts, pickleball courts, volleyball court, fishing pier, and playground equipment suitable for various ages including climbing wall. Dog-friendly with leash requirements. Safer alternative to larger lakeside parks with well-maintained facilities and family-friendly atmosphere.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great variety of activities in one place! The playground with climbing wall will challenge Yunsol, and the open spaces are perfect for running around. Feels safer and more contained than bigger parks.

places.name: Marymoor Park
places.description: 684-acre park featuring a spacious off-leash dog area, climbing wall, soccer fields & concerts. Perfect for families with pets and outdoor enthusiasts seeking diverse activities.
places.address: 6046 West Lake Sammamish Pkwy NE, Redmond, WA 98052
places.parkingInfo: Smart parking arrangements with multiple lots available. Food trucks often present
places.specialNotes: Open 24 hours. Features Jerry Baker Memorial Velodrome, climbing wall, and concert venue. Largest off-leash dog park in the area. Popular for concerts, cycling, and family activities. Food trucks available (tacos, BBQ, cupcakes, ice cream). Peak times 5-8 PM.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Huge open space perfect for running around! The climbing wall will be exciting for Yunsol. Dog park means lots of friendly dogs to see, but keep close watch.

places.name: Meydenbauer Bay Park
places.description: This 2.5-acre beach offers in-season swimming plus a fishing dock & play/picnic areas. Beautiful waterfront location with stunning sunset views and family amenities.
places.specialNotes: Open 7 AM-11 PM daily. Features lifeguarded swimming area (seasonal), fishing pier, and playground. Family bathrooms with changing areas available. Perfect for sunset viewing, kayaking, and water activities. Beach access for swimming and water play.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Beautiful sunset spot! Swimming area will be perfect for Yunsol in summer. The playground right by the water is ideal for keeping kids entertained.

places.name: Wilburton Hill Park
places.description: Wooded park with picnic areas, a soccer field & 2 baseball fields, a playground & trails. Adjacent to the beautiful Bellevue Botanical Garden for extended exploration.
places.parkingInfo: Abundant free parking available with good accessibility
places.specialNotes: Open 6:30 AM daily. Features fenced dog park, breathtaking bridge over babbling brook, and trails with steady uphill inclines. Adjacent to Bellevue Botanical Garden with seasonal Garden d'Lights display. Clean restrooms and well-maintained facilities.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The bridge will be exciting for Yunsol! Combined with the botanical garden, this could be a full day adventure. Great for nature walks and discovering plants.

places.name: Bellevue Square
places.description: Sprawling venue that includes retail shops, casual & upscale dining options & a comedy club. Upscale shopping destination with family amenities and entertainment.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking with valet parking options available
places.specialNotes: Open 10 AM daily. High-end shopping with Tesla store, Tommy Bahama, and Macy's. Children's play area available. Concierge services and well-maintained restrooms at every corner. Comedy club for evening entertainment.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great for rainy day backup! The children's play area will keep Yunsol busy while shopping. Lots of dining options when she gets hungry.

places.name: Killarney Glen Park
places.description: Compact, wooded community park with tennis courts, basketball hoops, picnic areas & a playground. Hidden gem just minutes from downtown Bellevue with peaceful trails.
places.specialNotes: Small but well-maintained park perfect for quick visits. Features tennis courts, basketball courts, and short walking trails among majestic trees. Very quiet and peaceful atmosphere. Note: Only portable restrooms available.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for a quick play session! The wooded setting feels magical and the playground is just the right size for Yunsol's age.

places.name: Chism Beach Park
places.description: Beautiful serene park in SE Bellevue with a beautiful beach and a playground for kids. More secluded location with tons of shade and peaceful atmosphere.
places.parkingInfo: Lots of parking available with good accessibility
places.specialNotes: Features lifeguarded swimming area, clean public restrooms, and historic Burrows Cabin. More secluded than other beach parks with excellent shade coverage. Popular for family picnics but tends to be busy - only one picnic table available.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The secluded feel is perfect for peaceful family time! Swimming area with lifeguards makes it safe for Yunsol. The shade will be great on hot days.

places.name: Luther Burbank Park
places.description: Visitors swim, boat & fish at this 7-acre lakefront park with a playground, dog run & wetlands area. Historic park on Mercer Island with diverse activities and beautiful lake access.
places.parkingInfo: Ample free parking available with easy access
places.specialNotes: Open 6 AM daily. Features Calkins Point Sand Beach, pickleball courts, and boardwalk trail. Year-round lake access for swimming and water activities. Community and event center on-site. Some areas may feel undermaintained according to recent reviews.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Sand beach will be amazing for Yunsol! The variety of activities means we can spend a whole day here. Boardwalk trail is perfect for stroller walks.

places.name: KidsQuest Children's Museum
places.description: Interactive educational exhibits staged indoors & outdoors, plus workshops & summer camps. Perfect hands-on learning environment designed specifically for children's exploration and discovery.
places.parkingInfo: Parking validation available at SalesForce building at 929 (confirmed by business)
places.specialNotes: Open 9:30 AM daily. Admission $16.75. Features multiple themed rooms including tots room with tractor and vegetables, grocery store play area, train tracks, and climbing areas. Birthday party hosting available. Various activities for different age groups.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect rainy day activity! The tots room sounds ideal for Yunsol's age. All the hands-on exhibits will keep her engaged and learning through play.

places.name: The Museum of Flight
places.description: Large educational museum with aircraft & space vehicles on display, plus historical exhibits. World-class aviation museum with impressive collection from historic warplanes to modern jets.
places.address: 9404 E Marginal Way S, Seattle, WA 98108
places.specialNotes: Open 10 AM daily. Admission $26.00. Features Aviation Pavilion, Charles Simonyi Space Gallery, and Wings Caf√©. LGBTQ+ friendly. Home to Air Force One, Concorde, and extensive aircraft collection. Gift shop and dining available on-site.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Airplanes will fascinate Yunsol! Great for inspiring interest in aviation and science. The large exhibits and interactive displays will capture her imagination.

places.name: Woodland Park Zoo
places.description: 92-acre zoo with nearly 300 species, a vintage carousel, summer concerts & an indoor play space. Well-designed habitats that mimic natural environments for animals and families.
places.parkingInfo: On-site parking available, can be busy during peak times
places.specialNotes: Open 9:30 AM daily. Admission $26.96. Features Zoomazium indoor play space, vintage carousel, and spacious animal enclosures. Summer concerts and special events. Food court and gift shops available. Interactive map with real-time location tracking.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Animals in natural habitats will be amazing for Yunsol! The indoor play space is perfect for breaks. Carousel ride will be a special treat!

places.name: Washington Park Arboretum
places.description: On the shores of Lake Washington, this 230-acre preserve features rare trees & a Japanese garden. Beautiful botanical wonderland perfect for peaceful walks and nature education.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking available across the street with easy access
places.specialNotes: Open 8 AM daily. Features Foster Point Trail, Arboretum Loop Trail, and Seattle Japanese Garden (separate admission). Great for walking, running, cycling, and kayaking. Playground available near parking area. Peak cherry blossom season is popular.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Free admission makes this perfect for frequent visits! The variety of trees and plants will spark Yunsol's curiosity about nature. Great for educational walks.

places.name: Pacific Science Center
places.description: Rotating science exhibits plus laser light shows, a tropical butterfly house & IMAX movie theaters. Interactive science museum designed to inspire curiosity and learning through hands-on exploration.
places.address: 200 Sue Bird Ct N, Seattle, WA 98109
places.parkingInfo: Multiple parking options available in Seattle Center area
places.specialNotes: Open 10 AM daily. Admission $27.45. Features IMAX theaters, Laser Dome, Tropical Butterfly House, and hands-on exhibits. Located in Seattle Center with easy access to other attractions. Maker space area and VR experiences available.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for curious minds! The butterfly house will be magical for Yunsol. Interactive exhibits mean she can touch and explore while learning about science.

places.name: Olympic Sculpture Park
places.description: An offshoot of the Seattle Art Museum, this park features numerous sculptures spread over 9 acres. Free outdoor art experience with stunning waterfront views and unique installations.
places.parkingInfo: Limited street parking available, consider public transit
places.specialNotes: Open 24 hours. Features Alexander Calder's The Eagle, Richard Serra's Wake, and PACCAR Pavilion. Stunning views of Seattle skyline, waterfront, and Olympic Mountains. Perfect for sunset viewing and art appreciation walks.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Free art experience with amazing views! The large sculptures will spark Yunsol's imagination. Perfect for short visits and introducing her to public art.

places.name: Seward Park
places.description: Wooded refuge boasting a 300-acre forest with hiking trails, walking paths, beaches & a playground. Large urban forest park with diverse ecosystems and family-friendly amenities.
places.address: 5900 Lake Washington Blvd S, Seattle, WA 98118
places.parkingInfo: Parking lot available but can be busy during peak times
places.specialNotes: Open 6 AM daily. Features Audubon Center, amphitheater, and multiple hiking trails. Swimming areas and beach access available. Popular for nature education and bird watching. Various trail difficulty levels available.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Huge forest in the city! Perfect for nature exploration and hiking with Yunsol. The Audubon Center will teach her about local wildlife and ecosystems.

places.name: Lake Sammamish State Park
places.description: 512-acre park with ample waterfront access & boat launch, plus seasonal kayak rentals & picnicking. Beautiful state park with extensive beach access and family recreation opportunities.
places.specialNotes: Open 6:30 AM daily. Discover Pass required. Features Sunset Beach, boat launch, and kayak rentals by Wheel Fun Rentals. Large grassy areas perfect for picnics. Well-maintained facilities with restrooms and boat washing station.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Amazing beach and swimming area! Kayak rentals could be fun when Yunsol is older. The large grassy areas are perfect for running around and playing games.

places.name: Crossroads Park
places.description: Neighborhood park with multiple playgrounds, sports courts, and community center. Great for toddlers with age-appropriate play equipment and open grassy areas.
places.specialNotes: Multiple playground areas for different ages. Basketball courts, tennis courts, and large open fields. Community center with restrooms and programs.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Multiple playgrounds mean variety! The toddler area looks perfect and there's plenty of space to run around safely.

places.name: Kelsey Creek Farm
places.description: Working farm with barnyard animals, walking trails, and seasonal activities. Perfect introduction to farm life for toddlers with friendly animals and educational programs.
places.specialNotes: Home to pigs, sheep, goats, chickens, and rabbits. Educational programs and seasonal events. Walking trails through the farm property.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect first farm experience! Animals are used to children and the setting is safe and educational. Great for teaching about farm animals.

places.name: Highland Community Center
places.description: Community center with indoor playground, classes, and activities for young children. Climate-controlled environment perfect for rainy days with toddler-specific programs.
places.specialNotes: Toddler programs, indoor playground area, and family activities. Classes for various age groups and skill levels.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great rainy day option! Indoor playground and toddler classes would be perfect for Yunsol to socialize and play safely.

places.name: Factoria Blvd Park
places.description: Small neighborhood park with toddler-friendly playground and walking paths. Quiet, safe environment perfect for young children to explore and play.
places.specialNotes: Small, intimate park perfect for toddlers. Safe playground equipment and peaceful atmosphere. Good for quick play sessions.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect size for Yunsol - not overwhelming but has everything she needs for a fun play session. Close to home for easy visits.

places.name: Redmond Town Center
places.description: Outdoor shopping center with family-friendly stores, restaurants, and seasonal events. Great for stroller walks with plenty of seating and activities for families.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking in large lots and garage
places.specialNotes: Outdoor shopping with wide walkways perfect for strollers. Seasonal events, farmer's market, and family-friendly restaurants.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great for combining shopping with family time! Wide walkways for stroller, and lots of places to sit and eat when Yunsol gets tired.

places.name: Robinswood Park
places.description: Large park with playground, tennis courts, and open fields. Beautiful views and well-maintained facilities make it perfect for family outings and active play.
places.specialNotes: Large playground with equipment for various ages. Tennis courts, basketball court, and large open fields for running and games.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Big playground with lots of variety! The open fields are perfect for Yunsol to run around freely and safely.

places.name: Sammamish River Trail
places.description: Paved trail perfect for stroller walks, biking, and family exercise. Beautiful riverside setting with multiple access points and rest areas along the way.
places.address: Multiple access points in Bellevue and Redmond
places.parkingInfo: Multiple parking areas along the trail
places.specialNotes: 11-mile paved trail along the Sammamish River. Perfect for stroller walks, with parks and playgrounds along the route.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for long stroller walks! Yunsol can see water, ducks, and nature while getting fresh air. Multiple stopping points for snacks.

places.name: Eastgate Park
places.description: Neighborhood park with playground and sports facilities. Well-maintained and family-friendly environment with easy access and good amenities.
places.specialNotes: Playground with age-appropriate equipment, basketball court, and open grassy areas. Quiet neighborhood setting.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Nice quiet park for peaceful play time. Good playground equipment and safe environment for Yunsol to explore.

places.name: Bothell Landing
places.description: Historic park with boardwalk, playground, and Sammamish River access. Beautiful setting with educational elements and family-friendly facilities.
places.specialNotes: Historic site with restored buildings, boardwalk along the river, playground, and picnic areas. Educational plaques and beautiful scenery.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The boardwalk will be exciting for Yunsol! River views and playground make it perfect for combining nature exploration with play time.

places.name: Bellevue Strawberry Festival Site
places.description: Home to the annual Strawberry Festival and year-round community events. Large open space with seasonal activities and family-friendly events throughout the year.
places.address: Crossroads Park, 16000 NE 10th St, Bellevue, WA 98008
places.specialNotes: Annual Strawberry Festival in June with rides, food, and activities. Other seasonal events throughout the year.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Festival atmosphere will be magical for Yunsol! Kid-friendly rides and strawberry treats - perfect summer family activity.

places.name: Clyde Beach Park
places.description: Small lakefront park with beach access and playground. Quiet, family-friendly environment perfect for peaceful water play and relaxation.
places.specialNotes: Small, intimate beach park with shallow water access. Playground and picnic tables. Less crowded than larger beach parks.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect size for Yunsol - not overwhelming like bigger beaches. Shallow water is safe for toddler water play.

places.name: Imagination Station at Crossroads
places.description: Indoor children's play space with toddler-specific areas, climbing structures, and educational toys. Safe, clean environment designed specifically for young children.
places.specialNotes: Indoor playground specifically designed for toddlers and young children. Soft play areas, educational activities, and parent seating.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect rainy day spot! Designed specifically for Yunsol's age group - safe, clean, and lots of age-appropriate activities.

places.name: Redmond Central Connector
places.description: Beautiful paved trail connecting downtown Redmond with parks and attractions. Perfect for family walks and bike rides with stroller-friendly surfaces.
places.specialNotes: 2.3-mile paved trail connecting downtown Redmond to Marymoor Park. Art installations and beautiful landscaping along the route.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great for stroller adventures! Art along the way will keep Yunsol interested, and we can end at Marymoor Park for playground time.

places.name: Bellevue Aquatic Center
places.description: Indoor swimming facility with toddler pool, family changing rooms, and swimming lessons. Perfect for introducing toddlers to water in a safe, supervised environment.
places.specialNotes: Dedicated toddler pool area, family changing rooms, and swimming lessons for young children. Clean, well-maintained facility.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for teaching Yunsol to swim! Toddler pool is just the right depth and temperature. Great for building water confidence.

places.name: Kirkland Marina Park
places.description: Waterfront park with playground, beach access, and beautiful lake views. Family-friendly environment with walking paths and picnic areas along Lake Washington.
places.parkingInfo: Paid parking available in downtown Kirkland
places.specialNotes: Beautiful waterfront location with playground, beach access, and walking paths. Close to downtown Kirkland shops and restaurants.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Gorgeous lake views and playground! Perfect for combining play time with beautiful scenery. Downtown Kirkland has great family restaurants nearby.

places.name: Juanita Beach Park
places.description: Large lakefront park with sandy beach, playground, and extensive picnic areas. One of the most popular family destinations with lifeguards and excellent facilities.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking but fills up quickly in summer
places.specialNotes: Large sandy beach with lifeguards, multiple playgrounds, picnic shelters, and walking trails. Very popular in summer.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Amazing sandy beach perfect for building sandcastles! Multiple playground areas and lifeguards make it safe and fun for all-day family adventures.

places.name: Mercer Island Community Center
places.description: Community center with indoor playground, toddler programs, and family activities. Climate-controlled environment with age-appropriate facilities and classes.
places.specialNotes: Indoor playground, toddler classes, and family programs. Well-maintained facilities with restrooms and snack areas.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great for rainy days! Indoor playground and toddler classes would be perfect for Yunsol to socialize and stay active year-round.

places.name: Issaquah Salmon Hatchery
places.description: Educational facility where families can learn about salmon life cycles and see fish up close. Interactive exhibits and outdoor viewing areas perfect for curious toddlers.
places.specialNotes: Best visited during salmon runs (September-November). Educational displays, viewing windows, and outdoor ponds to observe fish.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for teaching Yunsol about nature and fish! The viewing windows will fascinate her, and it's educational and fun.

places.name: Cougar Mountain Zoo
places.description: Small, intimate zoo specializing in endangered species. Perfect size for toddlers with close-up animal viewing and educational programs designed for young children.
places.specialNotes: Small zoo perfect for toddlers. Specializes in endangered species with educational programs. Less overwhelming than larger zoos.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect size zoo for Yunsol! Not overwhelming like big zoos, and she can see animals up close. Great for her first real zoo experience.

places.name: Issaquah State Park (Lake Sammamish)
places.description: Beautiful state park with beach access, playground, and nature trails. Excellent facilities and well-maintained grounds perfect for family camping and day trips.
places.specialNotes: Large beach area, playground, and hiking trails. Camping available. Well-maintained restrooms and picnic facilities.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Huge beach area perfect for all-day adventures! Playground and nature trails mean variety for Yunsol. Great for building outdoor confidence.

places.name: Redmond Saturday Market
places.description: Weekly farmers market with family-friendly atmosphere, local vendors, and seasonal activities. Great for introducing toddlers to fresh foods and community events.
places.specialNotes: Saturday mornings May through October. Local produce, crafts, and family activities. Music and seasonal events.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great for teaching Yunsol about healthy foods! She can see, touch, and taste fresh fruits and vegetables while enjoying the community atmosphere.

places.name: Snoqualmie Falls
places.description: Iconic 268-foot waterfall with viewing platform and easy walking trails. Spectacular natural attraction perfect for family photos and introducing toddlers to natural wonders.
places.parkingInfo: Free parking available but can be crowded
places.specialNotes: Easy viewing platform access. Gift shop and cafe on-site. Beautiful natural setting with short walking trails.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The waterfall will amaze Yunsol! Easy access and spectacular views. Perfect for teaching her about nature's power and beauty.

places.name: Northwest Railway Museum
places.description: Historic train museum with real locomotives and railway cars. Interactive exhibits and train rides perfect for toddlers fascinated by trains and transportation.
places.specialNotes: Historic trains, museum exhibits, and seasonal train rides. Thomas the Tank Engine events throughout the year.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect for Yunsol's love of trains! Real trains to explore and train rides will be magical for her. Educational and exciting!

places.name: Overlake Park
places.description: Neighborhood park with playground, sports courts, and open grassy areas. Well-maintained family-friendly environment perfect for active play and relaxation.
places.specialNotes: Playground with age-appropriate equipment, tennis courts, and large open fields for running and games.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Nice local park with good playground equipment. Open fields are perfect for Yunsol to run around and practice gross motor skills.

places.name: Bellevue Arts Museum
places.description: Contemporary art museum with family programs and interactive exhibits. Rotating exhibitions and hands-on activities designed to engage young children with art and creativity.
places.specialNotes: Family-friendly exhibitions, art-making activities, and special programs for young children. Modern, accessible facility.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Great for introducing Yunsol to art! Interactive exhibits and hands-on activities will spark her creativity and imagination.

places.name: Carillon Point Marina
places.description: Beautiful waterfront area with walking paths, restaurants, and lake views. Family-friendly environment perfect for stroller walks and enjoying the lakefront atmosphere.
places.specialNotes: Beautiful marina setting with restaurants, walking paths, and lake views. Family-friendly dining options available.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Beautiful place for stroller walks! Yunsol will love seeing the boats and water. Great for combining outdoor time with dining.

places.name: Gold Creek Park
places.description: Large park with multiple playgrounds, sports fields, and walking trails. Excellent facilities and diverse play areas perfect for families with children of different ages.
places.specialNotes: Multiple playground areas, sports fields, walking trails, and picnic facilities. One of the larger parks in the area.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Huge park with lots of variety! Multiple playgrounds mean Yunsol won't get bored, and there's plenty of space for all kinds of activities.

places.name: Phantom Lake Park
places.description: Scenic park with lake access, playground, and walking trails. Beautiful natural setting perfect for peaceful family outings and nature exploration.
places.specialNotes: Small lake with fishing access, playground, and walking trails. Peaceful setting away from busy areas.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Peaceful lake setting perfect for quiet family time! Yunsol can see ducks and fish while playing safely. Great for nature appreciation.

places.name: Tolt MacDonald Park
places.description: Large regional park with camping, playgrounds, and Snoqualmie River access. Adventure playground and suspension bridge make it exciting for active families.
places.specialNotes: Large park with suspension bridge, river access, camping facilities, and adventure playground. Great for all-day family adventures.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: The suspension bridge will be thrilling for Yunsol! Big adventure playground and river views make this perfect for building confidence and exploration.

places.name: Remlinger Farms
places.description: Working farm with seasonal activities, pumpkin patch, and family attractions. Perfect for introducing toddlers to farm life with rides, animals, and educational programs.
places.specialNotes: Seasonal farm activities, pumpkin patch, corn maze, farm animals, and rides. Special events throughout the year.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Perfect fall activity for Yunsol! Pumpkin picking, farm animals, and toddler-friendly rides. Great for creating seasonal family memories.

places.name: Beaver Lake Park
places.description: Beautiful forest park with lake access, playground, and walking trails. Peaceful natural setting perfect for nature exploration and outdoor play.
places.specialNotes: 2.5-mile loop trail around lake, playground, and picnic areas. Beautiful forested setting with wildlife viewing opportunities.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Loop trail is perfect for stroller walks! Yunsol will love seeing the lake and maybe spotting ducks or other wildlife. Great for nature education.

places.name: Pine Lake Park
places.description: Charming neighborhood park with playground, sports courts, and lake views. Family-friendly environment with well-maintained facilities and peaceful atmosphere.
places.specialNotes: Playground with lake views, basketball court, and walking paths. Quiet neighborhood setting with restrooms and picnic tables.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Beautiful lake views while playing! The peaceful setting is perfect for Yunsol to play without crowds. Great for quiet family time.

places.name: Sammamish Commons
places.description: Large community park with multiple playgrounds, sports fields, and event spaces. Modern facilities and diverse activities perfect for active families.
places.specialNotes: Multiple playground areas, sports fields, community center, and event pavilion. Host to seasonal events and festivals.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Multiple playgrounds mean endless variety! Modern equipment and lots of space for Yunsol to explore safely. Great for meeting other families.

places.name: Redmond Central Park
places.description: Urban park with playground, walking trails, and community gardens. Perfect blend of nature and city amenities with family-friendly facilities.
places.specialNotes: Playground, walking trails, community gardens, and open grassy areas. Close to downtown Redmond amenities.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Community gardens will teach Yunsol about growing food! Close to downtown for easy lunch stops. Great combination of play and learning.

places.name: Anderson Park
places.description: Spacious neighborhood park with playground, tennis courts, and large open fields. Well-maintained facilities in a quiet residential setting.
places.specialNotes: Playground, tennis courts, and large grassy fields. Quiet neighborhood park with restrooms and picnic tables.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Quiet neighborhood feel is perfect for relaxed play time. Large open fields are great for Yunsol to run around freely.

places.name: Grass Lawn Park
places.description: Community park with playground, sports courts, and community center. Family-oriented facilities with programs and activities for all ages.
places.specialNotes: Playground, basketball and tennis courts, and community center with programs. Large grassy areas for activities.

yunsolExperience.personalNotes: Community center programs could be great for Yunsol! Playground and open space provide variety for different activities.

places.name: Idylwood Beach Park

tips.title: Pack Smart
tips.description: Always bring snacks, water, extra clothes, and favorite comfort items. A well-packed bag can save the day!

tips.title: Time It Right
tips.description: Plan outings around nap times and meal schedules. Happy, well-rested toddlers make for better adventures!

tips.title: Safety First
tips.description: Research the venue beforehand, check for toddler-proofing, and always keep a close eye on your little explorer.

tips.title: Have a Backup Plan
tips.description: Weather changes, meltdowns happen! Always have an indoor alternative or know when it's time to head home.
